n-1
T
(n-1) \times (n-1)
X = \bigl( \begin{array}{cc}  1 & \overline{0} \\ T & \underline{0}   \end{array} \bigr) 
\mathcal{P}_n
P
(n-1) \times (n-1)
X \in \mathcal{T}_n
Y \in \mathcal{P}_n
YXY^{-1} \in \mathcal{T}_n
Y = \bigl( \begin{array}{cc}  1 &  \overline{0} \\ \underline{0} & P    \end{array} \bigr) 
 I(X,Y) = \left\{   \begin{array}{l l}     1 & \quad \text{if $YXY^{-1} \in \mathcal{T}_n$}\\     0 & \quad \text{otherwise}   \end{array} \right.
Z(n) = \sum_{X \in \mathcal{T}_n} \sum_{Y \in \mathcal{P}_n}  I(X,Y)
